c: 12
v: 80
t: "So when they despaired from him, they cleared secretly conversing, their oldest said: \"Did you not know that your father, had taken on you a promise/covenant from God and from before what you abused/exceeded the limit in (on) Joseph, so I will never/not leave/depart the land until my father permits/allows for me, or God judges/rules for me, and he (is) best (of) the judges/rulers"